#: ../../source/opac.rst:6
msgid "OPAC"
msgstr "公共目录检索"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:11
msgid "Search results"
msgstr "检索结果"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:13
msgid "To search the OPAC you can either choose to enter your search words in the box at the top of the OPAC or click on the 'Advanced search' link to perform a more detailed search."
msgstr "检索公共目录，需要在检索框输入关键词进行检索，或者点击“组合检索”链接进行更多条件组合的检索。"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:17
msgid "|image937|"
msgstr "|image937|"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:19
msgid "For more on searching check the '`Searching <#searching>`__' chapter in this manual."
msgstr "关于检索的更多信息可查阅手册的\"`检索 <#检索>`__\"章节。"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:25
msgid "Results overview"
msgstr "查看检索结果"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:27
msgid "After performing a search the number of results found for your search will appear above the results"
msgstr "在进行一次检索操作之后，检索结果数目会在检索结果上方显示"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:30
msgid "|image938|"
msgstr "|image938|"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:32
msgid "By default your search results will be sorted based on your :ref:`OPACdefaultSortField and OPACdefaultSortOrder <opacdefaultsortfield-and-opacdefaultsortorder-label>` system preference values. To change this you can choose another sorting method from the pull down on the right."
msgstr "检索结果默认会使用您在 :ref:`OPACdefaultSortField 和 OPACdefaultSortOrder <opacdefaultsortfield-and-opacdefaultsortorder-label>` 里设置的值进行排序，当然您可以单击右侧下拉菜单来改变顺序。"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:37
msgid "|image939|"
msgstr "|image939|"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:39
msgid "Under each title on your results list a series of values from your leader will appear. It is important to note that this has nothing to do with the item types or collection codes you have applied to your records, this data is all pulled from your fixed fields. This can be turned on or off with the :ref:`DisplayOPACiconsXSLT` system preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:46
msgid "|image940|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:48
msgid "Below each title you will see the availability for the items attached to the record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:51 ../../source/opac.rst:178 ../../source/opac.rst:195
#: ../../source/opac.rst:308 ../../source/opac.rst:912
#: ../../source/opac.rst:935 ../../source/opac.rst:1272
#: ../../source/opac.rst:1278
msgid "**Note**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:53
msgid "Even if you filtered on one library location all locations that hold the item will appear on the search results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:56 ../../source/opac.rst:293 ../../source/opac.rst:464
#: ../../source/opac.rst:550 ../../source/opac.rst:707
#: ../../source/opac.rst:1104 ../../source/opac.rst:1209
msgid "**Important**"
msgstr "**重要**"

#: ../../source/opac.rst:58
msgid "An item's hold status doesn't not affect whether or not the item is 'available' until the item is in 'waiting' status. Items with on-shelf holds will show as available until a librarian has pulled them from the shelf and checked the item in make it show 'waiting'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:63
msgid "|image941|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:65
msgid "If you have turned on :ref:`Enhanced content system preferences <enhanced-content-system-preferences-label>` preferences you may have book jackets on your search results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:68
msgid "|image942|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:70
msgid "If you have set your :ref:`Did you mean? <did-you-mean?-label>` options you will see a yellow bar across the top of your results will other related searches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:74
msgid "|image943|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:76
msgid "If you performed an advanced search you see an option to go back and edit your advanced search blow the list of results pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:79
msgid "|image1295|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:84
msgid "Filters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:86
msgid "To filter your results click on the links below the 'Refine your search' menu on the left of your screen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:89
msgid "|image944|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:91
msgid "Depending on your setting for the :ref:`DisplayLibraryFacets` system preference you will see filters for your home, holding or both libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:95
msgid "|image1296|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:97
msgid "After clicking a facet you can remove that filter from your results by clicking the small 'x' that appears to the right of the facet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:100
msgid "|image1297|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:105
msgid "Search RSS feeds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:107
msgid "You will be able to subscribe to your search results as an RSS feed by clicking the RSS icon in your address bar or next to the number of results. To learn more about what RSS feeds are check out `this tutorial video <http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0klgLsSxGsU>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:112
msgid "|image945|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:114
msgid "Subscribing to search results as RSS feeds will allow you to see when a new item is added to the catalog in your area of interest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:120
msgid "Bibliographic record"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:122
msgid "When you click on a title from the search results, you're brought to the bibliographic detail of the record. This page is broken down in several different areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:126
msgid "At the top of your screen will be the title and the GMD:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:128
msgid "|image946|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:130
msgid "Below the title the authors will be listed. These come from your 1xx and 7xx fields. Clicking the author will run a search for other titles with that author."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:134
msgid "|image947|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:136
msgid "If you have an authority file you will see a magnifying glass to the right of author (and other) authorities. Clicking that magnifying glass will take you directly to the authority record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:140
msgid "|image948|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:142
msgid "If you have your :ref:`DisplayOPACiconsXSLT` preference set to 'show' you will see a material type that is determined by values in your fixed fields (learn more in the :ref:`XSLT material type icons <material-type-cataloging-guide-label>` cataloging guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:147
msgid "|image949|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:149
msgid "Next you'll see the description of the record you're viewing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:151
msgid "|image950|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:153
msgid "Following that information you'll find the subject headings which can be clicked to search for other titles on similar topics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:156
msgid "|image951|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:158
msgid "If your record has a table of contents or summary it will appear next to the 'Summary' or 'Table of contents' label"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:161
msgid "|image952|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:163
msgid "If your record has data in the 856 fields you'll see the links to the right of the 'Online resources' label"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:166
msgid "|image953|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:168
msgid "If the title you're viewing is in a public list then you'll see a list of those to the right of the 'List(s) this item appears in' label and if it has tags they will appear below the 'Tags from this library' label"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:172
msgid "|image954|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:174
msgid "In the tabs below the details you will find your holdings data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:176
msgid "|image955|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:180
msgid "You can customize the columns of this table in the :ref:`'Table settings'<column-settings-label>` section of the Administration module (table id: holdingst)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:184
msgid "Any notes (5xx fields) that have been cataloged will appear under 'Title notes'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:187
msgid "|image956|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:189
msgid "If the bibliographic record is linked to a subscription in the :ref:`Serials module<serials-label>`, there will be a 'Subscriptions' tab with the subscription and issues information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:193
msgid "|image1498|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:197
msgid "You can customize the columns of this table in the :ref:`'Table settings'<column-settings-label>` section of the Administration module (table id: subscriptionst)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:201
msgid "If you're allowing comments they will appear in the next tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:203
msgid "|image957|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:205
msgid "And finally if you have enabled FRBR and you have other editions of the title in your collection you will see the 'Editions' tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:208
msgid "|image958|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:210
msgid "To the right of the details you'll find a series of boxes. The first box is a list of buttons to help navigate the search results. From there you can see the next or previous result from your search or return to the results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:215
msgid "|image959|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:217
msgid "Clicking 'Browse results' at the top of the right column will open up your search results on the detail page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:220
msgid "|image960|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:222
msgid "Below the search buttons you'll find the links to place a hold, print the record, save the record to your lists, add it to your cart or send to a device (using a QR code)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:226
msgid "Another option that will appear on this right hand side bar (if a library is allowing purchase suggestions) is the ability to 'Suggest for Purchase'.  Clicking this link will bring the user to the Purchase Suggestion form to fill out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:228
msgid "|image961|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:230
msgid "Clicking 'More searches' will show the list of libraries you entered in your :ref:`OPACSearchForTitleIn` preference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:233
msgid "|image962|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:235
msgid "Under the 'Save record' label you will find a series of file formats you can save the record as. This list can be customized by altering the :ref:`OpacExportOptions` system preference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:239
msgid "|image963|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:241
msgid "If at any time you want to change the view from the 'Normal' view to see the Marc or the ISBD you can click the tabs across the top of the record"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:244
msgid "|image964|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:249
msgid "Lists and the cart"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:251
msgid "A cart is a temporary holding place for records you're interested in finding during this session. That means that once you log out of the OPAC or close the browser you lose the items in your cart. A list is a more permanent location for saving items. To learn more about lists, check the `Lists in the staff client <#stafflists>`__ chapter of this manual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:261
msgid "Lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:263
msgid "Patrons can manage their own private lists by visiting the 'your lists' section of their account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:266
msgid "|image965|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:271
msgid "Creating lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:273
msgid "Lists can also be created by choosing the 'New list' option in the 'Add to' menu on the search results"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:276
msgid "|image966|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:278
msgid "To create a list the patron simply needs to click the 'New list' link and populate the form that appears"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:281
msgid "|image967|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:283
msgid "The only field required is the 'List name,' but the patron can also choose how they want the list sorted and if the list is public or private."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:287
msgid "A private list is managed by you and can be seen only by you (depending on your permissions settings below)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:290
msgid "A public list can be seen by everybody, but managed only by you (depending on your permissions settings below)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:295
msgid "If you aren't allowing patrons to create public lists with the :ref:`OpacAllowPublicListCreation` preference then patrons will only be able to create private lists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:299
msgid "|image968|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:301
msgid "Finally decide what your permissions will be on the list. You can all or disallow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:304
msgid "anyone else to add entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:306
msgid "anyone to remove his own contributed entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:310
msgid "The owner of a list is always allowed to add entries, but needs permission to remove."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:313
msgid "anyone to remove other contributed entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:318
msgid "Adding titles to lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:320
msgid "Titles can be added to lists from the search results and/or from the bibliographic record. On the search results options to add items to the list appear below each result and across the top of the results page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:324
msgid "|image969|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:326
msgid "To add a single title to a list, click the 'Save to lists' option and then choose the list you'd like to add the title to. To add multiple titles to a list check the boxes on the left of the titles you want to add and then choose the list you want to add the titles to from the 'Add too' pull down at the top of the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:335
msgid "Viewing lists contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:337
msgid "To view the contents of a list, click on the list name under the 'Lists' button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:340
msgid "|image970|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:342
msgid "The contents of the list will look similar to your search results pages except that there will be different menu options across the top of the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:346
msgid "|image971|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:348
msgid "To the right of the list title there is an RSS icon that will allow you to subscribe to updates to the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:351
msgid "Using the menu options above the list you can place multiple items on hold, download the list contents, email the list or print the list out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:354
msgid "To place a hold on one or more list items check the box to the left of the item and click the 'Place hold' link at the top"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:357
msgid "To download the list contents click the 'Download list' link and choose the format you'd like to download the list in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:360
msgid "To email the list contents to someone, click the 'Send list' link and enter in your email details in the form that pops up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:363
msgid "|image972|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:365
msgid "To print the contents of your list out click the 'Print list' link"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:370
msgid "Managing lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:372
msgid "Once the list is saved patrons can begin adding items to it. From the 'your lists' tab on the patron record the patron can edit and delete the lists they have created by clicking the appropriate link to the right of the list name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:377
msgid "|image973|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:379
msgid "To edit the list's title or sorting patrons click the 'Edit' link to the right of the list description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:382
msgid "|image974|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:384
msgid "When clicking 'Delete' next to a list you will be asked to confirm that you want to delete the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:387
msgid "|image975|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:389
msgid "The list will not be deleted until the 'Confirm' button is clicked to the right of the list you'd like to delete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:392
msgid "If the library is allowing you to share private lists with the :ref:`OpacAllowSharingPrivateLists` preference then you will see the 'Share' link on your list of lists and the 'Share list' link at the top of each individual list. Clicking this will ask you to enter the email address of a patron."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:398
msgid "|image1298|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:400
msgid "Once the email address is entered Koha will present you with a confirmation message"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:403
msgid "|image976|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:405
msgid "and will send a message to that patron."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:410
msgid "Cart"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:415
msgid "Adding titles to the cart"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:417
msgid "Titles can be added to the cart from the search results and/or from the bibliographic record. On the search results options to add items to the cart appear below each result and across the top of the results page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:421
msgid "|image977|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:423
msgid "Clicking the 'Add to cart' button will add the one title to your cart. To add multiple titles at once, check the box to the left of each result and then choose 'Cart' from the 'Add to' pull down at the top of the screen. Once titles are added to the cart you will be presented with a confirmation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:429
msgid "|image978|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:431
msgid "From the results you will see which items are in your cart and will be able to remove those items by clicking '(remove)'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:434
msgid "|image1299|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:439
msgid "Managing the cart"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:441
msgid "Once you have titles in your cart you can manage the contents by clicking on the 'Cart' button usually found at the top of the screen. Your cart will open in a new window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:445
msgid "|image979|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:447
msgid "From this window you are presented with several options. Across the top of the cart are several buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:450
msgid "First is the 'More details' button. Clicking this will show you additional information about the titles in your cart (ISBNs, subjects, publisher info, notes and more)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:454
msgid "|image1300|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:456
msgid "Next is the option to send the contents of your cart to an email address. This is handy if you want to send the resources you found at the library to your home email account to refer to later or to send to a patron researching a specific topic. Clicking this link will open up a new window that asks for the email address and message to send."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:462
msgid "|image980|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:466
msgid "The cart can only be emailed by logged in users. This will prevent your cart email function from being used for spamming."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:469
msgid "In addition to sending your cart you can download the contents of your cart in several pre-defined formats or using a :ref:`CSV profile <csv-profiles-label>` that you defined in the tools module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:473
msgid "|image981|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:475
msgid "Finally you can print out the contents of your cart by choosing the 'Print' link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:478
msgid "In addition to the various different ways to save the contents of your cart, there are ways to add value to the data in your cart. By selecting one or more titles from the cart you can add them to a list (click 'Add to a list'), place hold(s) (click 'Place hold'), or tag them (click 'Tag'). All of these operations follow the same procedure as they do when performing them in the OPAC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:488
msgid "Placing holds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:490
msgid "Patrons can place holds on items via the OPAC if they're logged in and you have the :ref:`RequestOnOpac` preference set to 'Allow'. If the item can be placed on hold the option to place it on hold will appear in several different places."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:495
msgid "When viewing a list or search results page you'll see the option to place hold on multiple items by checking the boxes to the left of the results and clicking 'Place hold' at the top"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:499
msgid "|image982|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:501
msgid "When viewing a list or search results page you'll see the option to place the item on hold below the basic information about the title"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:504
msgid "|image983|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:506
msgid "When viewing an individual title you'll see the option to place a hold in the box on the right side of the screen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:509
msgid "|image984|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:511
msgid "No matter which of the above links you click to place your hold you'll be brought to the same hold screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:514
msgid "|image985|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:516
msgid "Check the box to the left of the items you'd like to place on hold"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:518
msgid "The title includes a link back to the detail page for the record"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:520
msgid "The priority shows where in the holds queue this hold will fall"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:522
msgid "If allowed by your :ref:`OPACAllowUserToChooseBranch` preference the patron can choose where they'd like to pick up their hold. The list of available pickup locations will include all libraries that have 'Pickup location' set to 'Yes' on the library configuration page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:528
msgid "If you would like to see more options you can click 'Show more options'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:531
msgid "Place hold form with more options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:533
msgid "If you have the :ref:`AllowHoldItemTypeSelection` preference set to 'Allow' and the record had more than one item type attached you will see an option to choose to limit the hold to a specific item type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:539
msgid "|image1301|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:541
msgid "If allowed by your :ref:`OPACAllowHoldDateInFuture` preference, the 'Hold starts on date' column will show. This field allows the patron to have their hold start on a future date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:546
msgid "By default holds placed in the system remain until canceled, but if the patron fills in a 'Hold not needed after' date then the hold has an expiration date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:552
msgid "Expired holds are removed by the :ref:`expired holds cron job <cron-expired-holds-label>`, this is not an automatic process and must be set up by your system administrator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:556
msgid "If allowed by the :ref:`OpacHoldNotes` preference then patrons can leave notes about their holds for the library by clicking the 'Edit notes' button"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:560
msgid "|image986|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:562
msgid "Depending on the rules you set regarding item specific holds in your :ref:`circulation and fines rules <circulation-and-fines-rules-label>` the patron will be allowed to choose whether to place the hold on the next available copy and/or a specific copy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:567
msgid "|image987|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:569
msgid "After clicking the 'Place hold' button the patron will be brought to their account page where they'll see all of the items they have on hold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:575
msgid "Enhanced content"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:580
msgid "Tagging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:582
msgid "Depending on your settings for the :ref:`TagsEnabled`, :ref:`TagsInputOnList` and :ref:`TagsInputOnDetail` preferences you may be able to add tags to bibliographic records from the search results and/or bibliographic records. If you are allowing patrons to add tags from the search results screen you will see an input box below each result and a 'Tag' option at the top of the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:590
msgid "|image988|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:592
msgid "To add a tag to one item, type the tabs (separated by commas) in the 'New tag' box and click 'Add'. You will be presented with a confirmation of your tags being added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:596
msgid "|image989|"
