msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1161
msgid "|image1027|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1163
msgid "If you use an outside driver for sending text messages set with the :ref:`SMSSendDriver` preference, you will see an additional column to receive these messages as SMS (or text messages) and a field for a cell (or SMS) number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1168
msgid "|image1028|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1170
msgid "If you are using the Email protocol for sending text messages set with the :ref:`SMSSendDriver` preference, you will see an additional column to receive these messages as SMS (or text messages), a field for a cell (or SMS) number, and a pull down listing :ref:`cellular providers entered in administration <sms-cellular-providers-label>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1176
msgid "|image1029|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1178
msgid "If you are using the :ref:`Itiva Talking Tech <talkingtechitivaphonenotification-label>` service you will see an additional column to receive these messages via Phone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1182
msgid "|image1311|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1184
msgid "These notices are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1186
msgid "Advanced notice: A notice in advance of the patron's items being due (The patron can choose the number of days in advance)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1189
msgid "Item checkout: A notice that lists all the of the items the patron has just checked out and/or renewed, this is an electronic form of the checkout receipt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1193
msgid "Hold filled: A notice when you have confirmed the hold is waiting for the patron"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1196
msgid "Item due: A notice on the day and item is due back at the library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1198
msgid "Item check-in: A notice that lists all the of the items the patron has just checked in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/opac.rst:1201
msgid "Patrons can choose to receive their notices as a digest by checking the 'Digest only?' box along with the delivery method. A digest is a combination of all the messages of that type (so all items due in 3 days in one email) in to one email instead of multiple emails for each alert."
